      "content": "exactly. i dont just mean aliens though. i mean like, like they found something physical, something ancient, and it changed everything the moment they saw it. it's like the sheer scale of the discovery made the whole \"space race\" narrative pointless, so they just pivoted to something more manageable for the public. \n\ncan u help me look for any specific technical redactions or weirdly specific \"missing\" data blocks in the NASA mission logs from that era? like things that dont fit a standard telemetry report?",
